<item>
            <title>[LU-19214] default weighting for LND types</title>
                <link>https://jira.whamcloud.com/browse/LU-19214</link>
                <project id="10000" key="LU">Lustre</project>
                    <description>&lt;p&gt;If a client can connect to a server with both &lt;tt&gt;@tcp&lt;/tt&gt; and &lt;tt&gt;@o2ib&lt;/tt&gt; networks to a specific server, then all else being equal (network hops, interface speed) it makes sense for the client to prefer using the &lt;tt&gt;@o2ib&lt;/tt&gt; interface exclusively instead of trying to load-balance across the two network types.  The &lt;tt&gt;@o2ib&lt;/tt&gt; network will have both lower latency as well as lower CPU usage on both the client and server, so using &lt;tt&gt;@tcp&lt;/tt&gt; for some of the traffic will be counter-productive.&lt;/p&gt;</description>
